Enum Server

  • java.lang.Object
    • java.lang.Enum<Server>
      • application.Server
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.io.Serializable, java.lang.Comparable<Server>

    public enum Server
extends java.lang.Enum<Server>
    The main class of ChattApp 2.0 Server side. It uses the Singleton design pattern. Controls all the connection from the client to different servers.
    Author:
    Fredrik Johansson, Mattias Edin

      • isNickOccupied

        public java.lang.String isNickOccupied(java.lang.String nick)
        Checks to see if a nick is occupied among the connected clients in the client-list and returns a unique nick. A pair of nicknames counts as being equal if they are equal after using the method toUppercase on the pair.
        Parameters:
        nick - Preferred nickname.
        Returns:
        A unique nickname.

      • clientListRemove

        public void clientListRemove(ToClient o)
        Removes the first occurrence of the specified element from this list, if it is present. If the list does not contain the element, it is unchanged. More formally, removes the element with the lowest index i such that (o==null ? get(i)==null : o.equals(get(i))) (if such an element exists). Returns true if this list contained the specified element (or equivalently, if this list changed as a result of the call).
        Parameters:
        e - Element to be removed from this list, if present.
